aa(lp37
VAnd this isn't just a problem in Britain.
p38
aVIt's a problem across the developing world,
p39
aVand in middle income countries too. In Jamaica,
p40
aVfor example \u2014 look at Jamaican members of Parliament,
p41
aVyou meet them, and they're often people who are
p42
aVRhodes Scholars, who've studied at Harvard or at Princeton,
p43
aVand yet, you go down to downtown Kingston,
p44
aVand you are looking at one of the most depressing sites
p45
aVthat you can see in any middle-income country in the world:
p46
aVa dismal, depressing landscape
p47
aVof burnt and half-abandoned buildings.
p48
aVAnd this has been true for 30 years, and the handover
p49
aVin 1979, 1980, between one Jamaican leader who was
p50
aVthe son of a Rhodes Scholar and a Q.C. to another
p51
